<image 1> In data set A, the mean is

A. 3
B. 11
C. 12
D. 13
E. 18

To find the mean of data set A, we need to sum all the numbers in the data set and then divide by the number of numbers in the data set.

Data set A: 3, 4, 6, 12, 16, 17, 19

Sum of the numbers in data set A = 3 + 4 + 6 + 12 + 16 + 17 + 19 = 75

Number of numbers in data set A = 7

Mean of data set A = Sum / Number of numbers = 75 / 7 = 10.71

The closest answer choice is:

B. 11
